8. Sustained Emission Mechanism: The Ritual Mint

üìå Purpose

After the final halving phase (from 2036 onward), regular block rewards cease. To maintain validator incentives, ecosystem liquidity, and community engagement, GLC introduces a controlled minting mechanism ‚Äî the Ritual Mint.

This system allows for the creation of new GLC tokens under strict conditions, tied to PoF activity, validator performance, and community rituals.

---

üß¨ Core Principles

- Non-inflationary by design: Minting is capped and algorithmically regulated  
- PoF-linked: Only active validators participating in PoF cycles can trigger minting  
- NFT-gated: Requires possession of specific high-tier talismans  
- Community-approved: Minting events must pass decentralized voting via @GoodLuckBot

---

üìà Minting Parameters

| Parameter              | Value / Rule                          |
|------------------------|----------------------------------------|
| Max Annual Mint        | 0.5% of circulating supply             |
| Mint Trigger           | PoF validator cycle completion         |
